content.description: Sit start with your left hand on the arete and your right hand edge on the face. From there, bump through a right hand gaston to the hueco, bump your left hand up the arete, gain the lip, and mantel atop the boulder.
content.protection: A pair of pads. The landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs the north side of the northeast arete.

content.description: Sit start matched on the block edge. From there, gain a right hand edge, follow the hueco, reach a crimp far out right, bump the left hand up the hueco, stick the lip, and mantel atop the boulder.
content.protection: A pair of pads, but the landing is very good.
content.location: It climbs north face of Tres Huecos.

content.description: Sit start matched with a good diagonal rail and pasted feet. From there, dyno to the lip, and mantel on top of the boulder.
content.protection: A pad or two. The landing is shared with a rock.
content.location: This ascends the north face of Tres Huecos.

content.description:
Sit start matched on the block. From there, bump through a right hand edge to the hueco, gain the opposite hueco with the left hand, work into the underclings, snag the lip, and mantel on top.

It is difficult putting a grade on this one. The first move requires some horsepower, but the remainder is goes relatively easy.
content.protection: A pair of pads. It has a good landing.
content.location: It climbs the center of Tres Hueco's north face.
